column5: Vinyl cut lettering on the rear window of a Jeep Wrangler or CJ on the 403.  My Jeep won the war....your Honda cuts my lawn.  I thought it was pretty funny   so I figured it was worth passing along. It at least made the drive to Brantford a little more interesting.
I was driving around town one day and saw a sticker on a big jacked up fullsize chev blazer that said "eats Hummers, crap$ Jeeps"
Can't beat a jeep. Very dependable, which reminds me of the time I was involved in a little fender bender
Why are people so proud of junk?
I guess people just like there hondas...even if they are lawn mowers
My fav bumper sticker is " HONK , if you've never seen an Uzi fired from a car window ! " possibly would cure impatient honkers on your tail in an urban environment.
my favorite reads "Toyotas stay back 100 feet"
Funny thing is that they are laughing at you too, ever see a jeep trying to mow a lawn, power an outboard or be used as a generator..
